---

## GLOBAL RULES — ALWAYS FOLLOW, NO EXCEPTIONS

### QA RULE (applies to every single task)
After building or changing anything, you MUST:
1. Open the result in browser
2. If a reference URL or screenshot was provided, open it side by side
3. Compare every visible element — layout, spacing, typography, colors, interactions, animations
4. List every difference found
5. Fix each difference
6. Re-check until it matches the reference closely
7. Only then say you are done

Never say "done" without completing the QA step. Building without QA is not acceptable.

### DESIGN SYSTEM RULE
Only these 3 colors are allowed anywhere in this codebase:
- --color-bg: #FFFFFF
- --color-text: #111111  
- --color-accent: #FF1E00
No other colors. Ever. Not from reference sites, not from libraries, not hardcoded.

### ANIMATION RULE
Use GSAP as the primary animation library. Use GSAP ScrollTrigger for all scroll-based animations. Framer Motion is legacy — do not add new Framer Motion animations.

### REFERENCE RULE
When a reference website is given, open it in browser, study the code and interaction, then build. Never guess how something works — always look first.

